<p>That is what you're supposed to think.</p>
<p>However, if you read <a href="/gamedaypart1index">Game Day</a>, you'll see there is an alternative possibility:</p>
<p>699 is an infiltrator, and the report sent with it is a cover story, to induce the Foundation to keep it. It's not contained at all, and whatever is in the box can let itself out whenever it wants. It's waiting for <strong>something</strong> that hasn't happened yet, so is content to stay put in the box. The &quot;impossible to open&quot; part is not designed as containment, but to keep the Foundation from messing around with it.</p>

